The paper proposes a method for link prediction in graphs using a Gaussian process model that is transformed using simplified graph convolutions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of graph convolutions indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the evaluation of the model on large graphs with thousands of nodes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
